50|$|In the United States, topical <b>alitretinoin</b> (in {{the form}} of a gel; trade name Panretin) is {{indicated}} for the treatment of skin lesions in AIDS-related Kaposi's sarcoma. <b>Alitretinoin</b> is not indicated when systemic therapy against Kaposi's sarcoma is required. It has received EMA (11 October 2000) and FDA (2 March 1999) approval for this indication.|$|E
